# EvalForge Phase 2 Pre-Compact Handoff

Status: IN PROGRESS — context-preservation snapshot, not a completion claim.

## 1. Project Identity & Strategic Context

**Freshness: High - recently verified in this session.**

EvalForge is a local-first LLM evaluation dashboard in `/Users/fortunevieyra/Documents/Github/ai-projects/llm-evaluation-dashboard`. Phase 2 productizes the Phase 1 FastAPI, Streamlit, SQLite, and custom-metrics foundation into an easier, calmer B2B evaluation workspace. Success means a user can name an evaluation, check the setup, execute the candidate matrix, inspect immutable result evidence, and compare challengers against a baseline without unsupported claims. The visual philosophy is neutral, restrained, accessible, and intentionally avoids generic AI-product gradients, novelty copy, decorative glow, and ambiguous scores. Work remains local only; no hosted deployment, external provider call, billable usage, or production proof is authorized or claimed.

## 2. Current System State & Architecture Map

**Freshness: High - recently verified in this session.**

Implemented in the working tree: neutral Streamlit shell/theme; task-language navigation; named evaluation runs; candidate matrix preview; preflight applicability and estimates; completion-to-results action; truthful overview; run-detail evidence tabs and export controls; direction-aware metric presentation; baseline/challenger pairwise comparison; bounded paired case deltas; updated dashboard client; and supporting tests/docs. Flow: Streamlit UI -> typed dashboard client -> FastAPI routes -> service/evaluation engine -> SQLite persistence -> analytics/export read models. Analytics use only completed scored results and retain explicit denominators. Known Phase 1 boundaries remain: API auth/public exposure is deferred; paid provider proof and external CI are not Phase 2 completion requirements.

## 3. Critical Decisions & Reasoning History

**Freshness: High - recently verified in this session.**

The product now uses off-white canvas, white surfaces, ink/slate text, and one restrained teal accent rather than purple/cyan gradients. Navigation uses Home, Runs, Compare, New evaluation, Benchmarks, and Settings. Run names are part of both preflight invalidation and the create payload. The first candidate pair is visibly the baseline. Overview panels that implied global trends or leaderboard truth without supporting data were removed. Unknown cost stays unknown instead of becoming zero. Hallucination risk is rendered lower-is-better, while quality scores remain higher-is-better. Comparison reports pairwise denominators and case-level win/tie/loss evidence; it does not invent winner confidence. Immutable candidate labels and case identifiers are joined into result views.

